Nigeria Premier League side, Sunshine Stars Football Club of Akure are set to boost their squad with more strikers ahead of the second half of the season. A reliable source close to the team disclosed to DAILY POST that the former Shooting Stars gaffer has invited three new attackers to the team. The source added that Agoye is planning to improve the attack and give more competition to the team. “The coach has invited three players all attackers to train with the team ahead of the second half of the season, ” revealed the source. “He will make his decision after watching them closely in training.” The Akure club is looking to win its first NPFL title this season.